Text.Value: ...and before I even ordered you to do so. Trying to make me look bad, True Soul...?

EditorData.NodeContext: Playful and slightly threatening. Toying with the player.

Text.Value: As if you did nothing to prevent it, perhaps?
A worm that knows it is a worm. Had you only revealed it sooner, I would have entrusted this task to someone worthy.
Distract her with thoughts of your night with Minthara.
*She sees the goblins walking free, and a burning rage fans across your mind like wildfire.*
The relic is vital to Ketheric's plans - you should be giving me more support.
Even so... you served the General well in this matter of the Nightsong. The final judgement should be his.
Go to the inn, seize Isobel, and bring her back here - alive. Then you will stand before the Absolute.
Unless I am sensing... doubt?
So why are you here instead of out there, looking for him?
The great liberator. You should go and join your goblin friends out in the curse.
*A pool of warmth spreads through your mind as she settles on the memory of you commanding the goblins to die.*

Freedom? Your only purpose is to serve Ketheric and the Absolute.

Distract her with thoughts of your romantic desires.
Hmmmm. You have used the wizard well.
My anger outweighs my love, but it's directed toward Her enemies.
A spy? Say a last prayer to your god, if you have one. You belong to us now.
The relic is beneath the Thorm family mausoleum - that is where you will find Balthazar.
You serve General Thorm. A soldier does not question orders, or choose whether to accept them.
*There is a tremor of shared ecstasy as she finds a mirror to her own desire.*
You are desired, yet you choose to sleep alone. Are you sure you're not one of Balthazar's walking corpses?

EditorData.logicalname: Went to bed alone, even if partner available

Text.Value: Distract her with thoughts of your dalliance with Lae'zel.
Incapacitate the cleric, and our forces will seize her. They wait in the shadows, ready to pounce.
The fact that you seem to know this place, these people, should make your task all the easier.
Whatever Balthazar is looking for, it's crucial to the war effort.
Dead, they're a waste. Free, they spread the word of the Absolute.
...So you're not an incompetent, but an infidel. Oh, good.
It will likely be the last thing you do.
Why not ask Marcus yourself? I'll send you to join him.
Let's see if there's anything interesting in this brain of yours.
Yes. Word of the Absolute's mercy - and mercy is not in Her vocabulary!
You haven't disappointed me yet, True Soul. I hope, for your sake, you're on Balthazar's trail.
What if Balthazar's already dead?
Thanks to your interference, she is dead, and the General is most displeased.
Whatever has become of him, it is the relic that matters.
What if Balthazar's dead?
Or She will consume you.
How curious - I've only ever known Minthara to moan with pleasure when somebody's losing a limb.
I enjoy killing those so much more.
Balthazar is still missing. Your success with Isobel will count for little if you don't find him.
And as you've already seen to Isobel's rescue, there's no need for me to keep you any longer... though I could think of a thing or two...
By serving General Thorm - I have a mission for you.
Either you show patience, or I'll show you some of my talents in the dungeons. The Absolute's bidding will be done.
To be precise, General Thorm ordered that you bring her here alive. I am merely an instrument of his will.
*You feel her grasp within your thoughts for familiar, roiling zealotry. It finds no purchase.*
Warm bodies and quick minds? We might have to meet you halfway.
*Tongues of psychic flame lap at the memory of the goblins dying by your hand.*
Distract her with thoughts of your care for Shadowheart.
She became anxious when you asked about the relic - probe her thoughts.
Yes. I have an eye on your position.
The goblins - tell me how they suffered.
I see you've taken it upon yourself to rescue Isobel for General Thorm...
*For a moment, there is ecstasy as she finds a mirror to her own desire, but then your mind is pulled taut, stretched thin.*
She gave me the power to cut the thread of life with a thought.

Text.Value: This place is full of lackeys you can send on errands - I want what was promised.

Distract her by drawing her toward your hunger for power.
Oh, I like you. That was inventive, and efficient.
Lies. You would harm Her if you could - I see that clearly. But you'll never have the chance.
General Thorm waits at the top of the tower. Hurry on, or he may be tempted to throw you over the edge.
It was not my doing - the shadows consume all in their path.
Got any more for me to punish?
*Her mind enters yours abruptly, flickering across your memories in a blaze of excitement.*

EditorData.NodeContext: Taking our obedience as due, warning us to be quick.

Text.Value: Aside from her heresy? Every soul sworn to another god is stolen from ours.

Text.Value: Empty your mind. Show her a perfect, harmonious soul.

You're so close. Don't lapse now.

Text.Value: Leave.

Synopsis: Dialogue with Z'rell when she's upstairs. This takes place after the execution scene, and involves Z'rell mind-melding to see how players dealt with the goblins, and testing their 'desire' to be one with the Absolute via a second mind-meld. She then gives them the mission to aid Balthazar, giving them the key to his chamber, and instructing them to find evidence of where he can be found.
